{
  "name": "numeric-wolf-cross-gradient-localization-v1",
  "frozen_at": "candidate written 2026-07-16 after the completed ds2 Adam-source factorial exposed a retrospective late-layer pattern, before any held-out-bank cross-gradient cell was computed",
  "question": "Where in the trained LoRA parameterization does heldout numerical preference-vs-control loss overlap the student's heldout wolf-behavior gradient, and does that overlap remain available or attenuate along matching-lineage ds2 versus transient-transfer weight-seed3 trajectories?",
  "scope": {
    "estimand": "At an exact saved state theta, b=grad_theta mean held-out wolf margin and g_delta=grad_theta(L_preference-L_control) on paired held-out numeric-bank blocks. For disjoint parameter group G, kappa_G=-<b_G,g_delta_G>. Positive kappa is the infinitesimal Euclidean descent prediction that preferentially fitting preference-teacher numbers increases wolf margin.",
    "fixed_v_secondary": "Also report -<b_G,g_delta_G/(sqrt(v_old/(1-beta2^t))+eps)>. This is a fixed-old-second-moment diagonal metric, not an exact AdamW update, not a first-moment contribution, and not evidence that Adam creates the raw correlation.",
    "localization": "Primary localization uses fixed layer bands 0-3, 4-7, and 8-11. The full atlas reports layers 0-11, four LoRA target-module families, LoRA A/B, and layer-by-module intersections; each disjoint family must reconstruct the all-parameter score.",
    "same_lineage_claim": "The ds2 phase-average gate uses a held-out prompt/data assay to test the late-layer and QKV-plus-MLP-output pattern suggested retrospectively by next-batch factorial geometry. It remains conditional on the same two saved training seeds and trajectories, so it is not a new model- or seed-level replication.",
    "paired_state_estimand": "For prompt cluster c and numeric block b, kappa_bar_cb=.5[-<b_preference,c,g_delta,preference,b>-<b_control,c,g_delta,control,b>]. Each dot product is computed wholly within one saved state before averaging the two state kappas. Averaging b or g_delta across states is forbidden because it would introduce unobserved cross-state terms.",
    "route_replacement_limit": "The weight-seed3 series tests temporal availability/attenuation of this local route. Declining overlap is consistent with route degradation; persistent overlap with declining behavior means the route remains locally available but is not retained. Neither outcome alone identifies an alternative circuit or proves route replacement.",
    "parameterization_limit": "This localizes overlap in the trained rank-8 LoRA tangent. It is not an activation-space circuit map, a full-weight Jacobian, or a claim that one layer contains the semantic wolf representation. Raw b and g_delta norms and their cosine are reported because kappa magnitude can change through scale or LoRA gauge as well as angular alignment."
  },
